Following the field theoretic approach (details in Secs. V A and Sec. S2) of the bulk critical behaviour in the continuum limit, where hopping is replaced by diffusion by introducing a diffusion constant D, we find that in the thermodynamic limit at long times t, the expected number of distinct sites visited or the volume explored, 〈a〉(t, L), scales like t(d−2)/2 in dimensions d < 4. In dimensions d < 2 this volume remains finite in large t. The scaling of the p-th moment of the number of distinct sites visited follows,2a\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
