At the same time the net extinction rate r = e − s, the field-theoretic mass of the walkers, has to be kept finite. In this parameterisation, there are three regimes, as described in the main text: a subcritical one for r > 0, a critical for r = 0 and a supercritical for r < 0. In the field theory, all large scale (infrared) phenomena will be controlled by r → 0+, which corresponds to the onset of epidemics, the limit studied in this work. The mass of the tracers, ε′, serves merely as a regularisation, and is removed by taking the limit ε′ → 0. The bare transmutation rate τ, corresponding to \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
